zation without producing guilt or overload.
+
+Requirements:
+
+- capture an interaction in about 30 seconds;
+- show why a person is in a queue;
+- remember unfinished form state;
+- return the user to the exact place after interruption;
+- permit small capacity-limited review batches;
+- avoid a permanent red “overdue” debt counter by default;
+- allow cadences to be disabled;
+- use plain action language;
+- provide comfortable and compact density;
+- support reduced motion and low-stimulation mode;
+- let users hide low-priority sections;
+- offer one action at a time in guided review;
+- make skip, snooze, pause, archive, and do-not-contact first-class valid actions;
+- distinguish reminders from obligations;
+- preserve a searchable record so the user does not need to rely on working memory;
+- avoid gamification based on number of people contacted.
+
+The product should help the user act according to their values and capacity. It should not optimize for maximum interaction volume.
+
+---
+
+## 12. Privacy and safety boundaries
+
+- Sensitive Topic Packs are private or sealed by default.
+- A relationship assessment belongs to the authoring scope, not to the person being assessed.
+- Shared workspaces receive only explicitly shared fields and records.
+- AI tools receive only selected fields after policy evaluation.
+- Files and URLs are not fetched or transmitted without permission.
+- “Unknown,” “declined,” and “not applicable” remain distinct.
+- Health-adjacent, dietary, family, access, and travel data support purpose and retention rules.
+- Review scores and formulas are local, inspectable, and exportable.
+- Deleting the disposable index does not delete scores, policy definitions, or canonical evidence.
+- Relationship-review history may be retained privately and excluded from subject-facing exports where lawful and configured.
+
+---
+
+## 13. Bounded contexts
+
+### Identity and Profiles
+
+Owns Person identity, contact channels, Topic Pack assignments, field values, provenance, photos, and profile templates.
+
+### Organizations and Groups
+
+Owns Organizations, Groups, Households, memberships, departments, locations, and organization hierarchy.
+
+### Relationships
+
+Owns relationship edges, type definitions, relationship intent, boundaries, manual assessment snapshots, and graph queries.
+
+### Interactions and Commitments
+
+Owns interactions, communication logs, tasks, commitments, reminders, and next steps.
+
+### Events and Calendar
+
+Owns events, attendance, calendar source links, recurring occurrences, and event-specific readiness.
+
+### Knowledge and Resources
+
+Owns notes, files, URLs, attachments, backlinks, resource metadata, and safe previews.
+
+### Review and Attention
+
+Owns review policies, cadence evaluation, review-priority calculation, profile readiness, queues, review sessions, snoozes, and explanation generation.
+
+### Customization
+
+Owns Topic Pack definitions, field schemas, profile layouts, saved views, formula definitions, and plugin contributions.
+
+No connector or UI surface may calculate relationship status independently from the Review and Attention application services.
+
+---
+
+## 14. Example machine-readable policy
+
+```yaml
+schema: liaison/review-policy@1
+id: personal-balanced
+name: Personal balanced review
+mode: weighted
+scope:
+  entity_types: [person]
+  exclude_states: [archived, do_not_contact]
+capacity:
+  daily_maximum: 5
+  weekly_maximum: 20
+components:
+  - id: cadence
+    weight: 0.30
+    curve: cadence_ratio
+  - id: manual_importance
+    weight: 0.20
+    tier_values:
+      core: 100
+      active: 75
+      warm: 50
+      loose: 25
+  - id: open_commitments
+    weight: 0.20
+  - id: upcoming_dates
+    weight: 0.10
+    window_days: 30
+  - id: stale_required_context
+    weight: 0.10
+    readiness_purpose: general_relationship_review
+  - id: manual_boost
+    weight: 0.10
+explanations: required
+allow_hidden_components: false
+```
+
